PRESIDENT John Magufuli has sent his condolences to family, Chief Justice (CJ) Prof Ibrahim Juma and Anglican worshippers in Tanzania, following the demise of retired Chief Judge Augustino Ramadhani. Ramadhan who served in the capacity of Chief Justice from 2007 to 2010, passed away early on Tuesday at Aga Khan Hospital in Dar es Salaam. According to a press statement issued by the State House, President Magufuli said the deceased Justice will be remembered for his distinguished service, truth, hardworking, patriotism and God fearing man. “I’m deeply saddened by the news of Rtd CJ Augustino Ramadhani passing. I would like to send my condolences to his family, honorable Judges and judicial servants,” the statement added. Former President Jakaya Kikwete awarded Justice Augustino Ramadhani the ‘’Order of the Union’’ Medal for distinguished service to his country in 2014, when Tanzania Mainland celebrated her 53rd Independence Anniversary. Kenyan President Mwai Kibaki appointed the former President of the African Court on Human and Peoples’ Rights (AfCHPR) Justice Ramadhan to chair a seven-member tribunal to investigate the conduct of Kenya's Deputy Chief Justice, Nancy Baraza, regarding a gun incident in Gigiri, Nairobi last month.   